      <div class="section" id="explore-connections">
        <section>
          <h1>An outliner without the hierarchy.</h1>

          <p>Outliners like <a
          href="https://workflowy.com/" class="external-app-link"><span>Workflowy</span></a> are more
          convenient than other note-taking tools, but they have one problem:
          people don't think in lists. Thinktool looks like an outliner, but it
          structures your thoughts like a graph, so you can freely connect any
          item to any other item.</p>

          <div class="video-container">
            <iframe src="https://www.youtube.com/embed/anFFddA4Fm4" frameborder="0" allowfullscreen></iframe>
          </div>
        </section>
      </div>

      <div class="section" id="try-it">
        <section>
          <h1>Give it a try.</h1>
          <p>I'm currently developing Thinktool. Therefore, it's quite
          unstable, and the current preview is mainly intended for testing.</p>
          <p>That being said, you can try it out now, and if you like it, you
          can <a href="/login.html"><span>sign up</span></a> for an account.
          The preview is currently free, but Thinktool may become a paid
          subscription service in the future. Click the button below to check
          out a free demo in your browser:</p> <a href="/demo.html"
          class="demo">Open demo</a>
        </section>
      </div>

      <div class="section" id="similar-tools">
        <section>
          <h1>Alternatives to Thinktool.</h1>

          <p>Thinktool is directly inspired by outliners like
          <a href="https://orgmode.org/" rel="nofollow" class="external-app-link"><span>Org mode</span></a>,
          <a href="https://workflowy.com/" rel="nofollow" class="external-app-link"><span>Workflowy</span></a> and
          <a href="https://dynalist.io/" rel="nofollow" class="external-app-link"><span>Dynalist</span></a>,
          but Thinktool uses a more powerful data model underneath.</p>

          <p><a href="https://roamresearch.com/" rel="nofollow"
          class="external-app-link"><span>Roam</span></a> is another unusual
          outliner that tries to solve the same problems as Thinktool but takes
          a different approach.</p>

          <p>Thinktool structures your data in a similar way to <a
          href="https://thebrain.com/"
          class="external-app-link"><span>TheBrain</span></a>, but while
          Thinktool looks like an outliner, TheBrain looks like a mind-map.</p>
        </section>
